<br/></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p id='SURACAlxNNz' class='line'>These costs ARE variable, because we can still start a cloud with fewer than 100 Bpi boards, and we do not NEED to purchase sample phones or tablets.  This said, if we are to pursue the strategy discussed earlier regarding a move towards a branded HW/SW experience, then it is highly prudent to purchase devices as samples and ensure that they are used.  It is likely that our large purchase of devices will not be for another 2-3 months, when the Chinese will have updated their models.  This is so that we can get a picture of the relative quality of the products, and likely do some reverse engineering on them to ensure that we fully understand their electronic and software systems.  The vendor that comes out the best in our comparison will likely be the one who becomes our long-term partner.  I will not be going to china and speaking with random companies about partnering, but instead talking with ones that I have a pre-existing relationship with, and some other new firms that have popped up in the past year and make promising hardware.  </p>

<p id='SURACAkUTBK' class='line'>​</p>

